'''Transparency Options''' allow you to change the opacity of buildings and other map features. Each transparency option can be toggled by clicking on its specific button or using '''ctrl''' + ('''1''' to '''9'''). All [[en/Manual/Transparency options#locked-transparency-options|unlocked transparency options]] can be quicky toggled on/off by pressing '''X'''.

==Transparency Options Toolbar==
[[File:en/Manual/TransparencyOptions.png]]
The Transparency Options toolbar has two rows:
*The first row defines what map feature is affected, and if it is locked.
*The second row defines what map feature should be invisible when the first row is set.

